Package com.example.scandroid

Class User

java.lang.Object
com.example.scandroid.User
public class User extends Object
Represents a User in the scANDROID app for CMPUT 301 at UofA W24.
This class may represent a user with different permission levels - such as an Admin or an organizer or attendee.
Users are stored via a UserDB object.

    • User

      public User(String userID, String userName, String userPhoneNumber, String userAboutMe, String userEmail)
      Sole constructor for the User object, specifying user attributes.
      Parameters:
      userID - The user's ID generated upon boot. Accessed via Settings.Secure.ANDROID_ID
      userName - The name of the User object you want to instantiate. This is set to a random guest name if none is provided.
      userPhoneNumber - The phone number of a user object. May be null.
      userAboutMe - The about-me section of a user's profile. May be null.
      userEmail - The email address of a user object. May be null. * @param profilePictureUrl The URL of the user's profile picture. May be null.
